subSubSection.paragraph:
Hypopygium
(
Fig. 13E
). Tergite IX with 13–14 (2) setae, laterosternite IX with 1–4, 2 setae. Anal point (
Fig. 13D
) with distinct median furrow; 52–75, 68 µm long; 40–68, 48 µm wide at base, 20–26, 24 µm at apex; median furrow 9–11, 10 µm long. Transverse sternapodeme 47–58, 52 µm long; phallapodeme 58–86, 65 µm long. Gonocoxite 133–158, 150 µm long. Superior volsella (
Figs 13G–I
) 37–49, 44 µm long; base with microtrichia and 3–4 inner setae; projection needle-like, apex with 1 seta. Inferior volsella (
Fig. 13F
) 78–96, 85 µm long; parallel-sided and slender, with 1 prominent apical seta. Gonostylus slender, 105–125, 119 µm long. HR 1.21–1.31, 1.26; HV 2.11–2.26 (2).
